title: Ceiling Medallion, 1875–1906
creditline: Museum purchase from Smithsonian Institution Collections Acquisition Program and Sarah Cooper-Hewitt Funds
description: Set within a square framework, central stylized floral motif, surrounded by pink roses, small blue flowers and fern fronds. Three smaller square frameworks are directly opposite. The frame on either end containing a large pink rose, while the middle square contains a diagonal band.

tombstone.epitaph:
Ceiling Medallion, 1875–1906.
1875–1906. Block-printed. Museum purchase from Smithsonian Institution Collections Acquisition Program and Sarah Cooper-Hewitt Funds. 1995-165-9.
